The paper discusses machine learning methods for enforcing group parity or fairness, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the unintended behaviors that can arise when incorporating constraints, which could fall under the categories of cybersecurity (cs.CR) or social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper proposes a theoretical method for enforcing slack-consistency, which could fall under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
